-- Stock Exchanges to Start Pre-Open Call Auctions on Oct. 18, Express Says
-- B y   K e t a k i   G o k h a l e
-- 2010-10-08T14:49:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/stock-exchanges-to-start-pre-open-call-auctions-on-oct-18-express-says.html
The National Stock Exchange and the
Bombay Stock Exchange will start a 15-minute pre-trading session
from Oct. 18, the Indian Express reported, citing  Ravi Narain ,
managing director of the National Stock Exchange.  The session will be a call auction, where participants
place orders before the opening of trade and will run from 9 a.m.
to 9:15 a.m., the newspaper said.  The two bourses will introduce the session on a “pilot”
basis, and only stocks on the Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive
Index and S&P CNX  Nifty  Index will be available for trading, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Ketaki Gokhale  in Mumbai 
 kgokhale@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Foxwell at 
 sfoxwell@bloomberg.net . 